    <title id="1">Conref steps: assigning a new host node</title>
    <shortdesc id="2">You can use <nameliteral id="3">controller-0</nameliteral> to
        assign a configuration or <term id="4">personality</term> (controller, compute, or
        storage, for example) to a new node.</shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <author id="5">Jim Owens</author>
    </prolog>
    <rcbody>
        <context id="context_N10027_N10024_N10001" id="6">
            <p id="7">You can assign one of the following personalities.</p>
            <simpletable id="simpletable_ysx_xr5_k4">
                <strow>
                    <stentry id="8">
                        <p id="9">controller</p>
                    </stentry>
                    <stentry id="10">
                        <p id="11">redundant controller for failover</p>
                    </stentry>
                </strow>
                <strow>
                    <stentry id="12">
                        <p id="13">compute</p>
                    </stentry>
                    <stentry id="14">
                        <p id="15">processing node</p>
                    </stentry>
                </strow>
                <strow>
                    <stentry id="16">
                        <p id="17">storage</p>
                    </stentry>
                    <stentry id="18">
                        <p id="19">data storage node </p>
                    </stentry>
                </strow>
            </simpletable>
        </context>
        <prereq id="prerequisites" id="20">
            <p id="111">Before initializing a node, ensure that the following conditions are
                satisfied:</p>
            <ul id="ul_adx_kts_v4">
                <li id="112">
                    <p id="prereq-hw-requirements" id="21">The node must meet the hardware
                        requirements for the personality to be assigned.</p>
                </li>
                <li id="113">
                    <p id="prereq-controller-0-ready" id="23">Controller-0 must be installed
                        and configured.</p>
                </li>
                <li id="114">
                    <p id="prereq-computing-node-PXE-connected" id="26">The node must be
                        connected to the internal management network using an Ethernet interface
                        configured for PXE boot.</p>
                </li>
                <li id="129">
                    <p id="130">The node must be configured in the BIOS to boot from the internal management
                        network.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </prereq>
        <steps id="steps_N100AB_N10029_N10001">
            <step id="boot-node" id="30">
                <cmd id="31">Boot the new node using PXE.</cmd>
                <info id="32">
                    <p id="33">With <nameliteral id="34">controller-0</nameliteral>
                        running, start the node.</p>
    <!-- p><nameliteral>controller-0</nameliteral> accepts the PXE request from the
                        host node, configures the node's IP address, and pushes a network
                        bootstrap program.</p -->
    <!-- draft-comment>Jim - too much detail?</draft-comment -->
                    <p id="35">The node boots from the network.</p>
                    <fig id="fig_N100BC_N100A9_N100A1_N10091_N10024_N10001" id="36">
                        <image alt="Waiting for this node to be configured." href="jow1404333500016.image" id="image_whb_vjd_gn" id="37" width="4in"/>
                    </fig>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="assign-personality" id="38">
                <cmd id="39">Using the web management interface, assign the required personality to the node.</cmd>
                <substeps id="substeps_cdx_ds4_k4">
                    <substep id="open-hosts-list" id="40">
                        <cmd id="open-hosts-lists-cmd" id="41">Select the <uicontrol id="42">Hosts</uicontrol> list.</cmd>
                        <info id="43">
                            <p id="44">On the <uicontrol id="45">Admin</uicontrol> tab, in the <uicontrol id="46">System
                                    Panel</uicontrol> section, click
                                    <uicontrol id="47">Inventory</uicontrol>, and then select the
                                    <uicontrol id="48">Hosts</uicontrol> tab.</p>
                        </info>
                        <stepresult id="106">
                            <p id="open-hosts-lists-new-node" id="49">The new node is listed
                                with an empty <uicontrol id="50">Host Name</uicontrol> and
                                    <uicontrol id="51">Personality</uicontrol>.</p>
                            <fig id="fig_N10108_N100E4_N100D7_N100D3_N100CB_N10091_N10024_N10001" id="52">
                                <image href="jow1404333501487.image" id="image_yld_2zd_gn" id="53" width="6in"/>
                            </fig>
                        </stepresult>
                    </substep>
                    <substep id="click-edit-hosts" id="54">
                        <cmd id="cmd_assign_personality" id="55">Assign the node's personality.</cmd>
                        <info id="56">
                            <p id="p_click_edit_host" id="57">Click <uicontrol id="58">Edit Host</uicontrol> for the new host. </p>
                        </info>
                        <stepresult id="107">
                            <p id="108">The <wintitle id="131">Edit Host</wintitle> window
                                appears.</p>
                            <fig id="fig_N10129_N1011E_N10116_N100D3_N100CB_N10091_N10024_N10001" id="59">
                                <image href="jow1404333503033.image" id="image_wfz_h54_k4" id="60" width="4in"/>
                            </fig>
                        </stepresult>
                    </substep>
                    <substep id="select-personality" id="61">
                        <cmd id="62">Select the <uicontrol id="63">Personality</uicontrol> for the new node.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep id="specify-location" importance="optional" id="64">
                        <cmd id="65">Type a physical <uicontrol id="66">Location</uicontrol> for the node to help
                            identify it.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep id="save-personality-selection" id="67">
                        <cmd id="cmd-save-personality" id="68">Click <uicontrol id="69">Save</uicontrol> to initialize and configure the new
                            node.</cmd>
                        <stepresult id="109">
                            <p id="p-save-personality" id="71">The node is restarted
                                automatically, and a display-device menu appears on the node
                                console.</p>
                            <fig id="fig_N10166_N1015E_N10152_N100D3_N100CB_N10091_N10024_N10001" id="72">
                                <image href="jow1404333504524.image" id="image_j3g_rz4_k4" id="73" width="4in"/>
                            </fig>
                        </stepresult>
                    </substep>
                    <substep id="select-display-device" importance="optional" id="89">
                        <cmd id="90">Select the display device to use during initialization. </cmd>
                        <info id="91">
                            <p id="132">The personality (<nameliteral id="133">Controller</nameliteral>,
                                    <nameliteral id="134">Compute</nameliteral>, or
                                    <nameliteral id="135">Storage</nameliteral>) is confirmed in the
                                menu.</p>
                            <dl id="display-device-choices">
                                <dlentry id="74">
                                    <dt id="75"><nameliteral id="76">1) Serial
                                            &lt;personality&gt; Node Install</nameliteral>
                                        (default)</dt>
                                    <dd id="77">
                                        <p id="78">Use the serial port to display messages.
                                            You can monitor the port using the terminal server.</p>
                                    </dd>
                                </dlentry>
                                <dlentry id="79">
                                    <dt id="80"><nameliteral id="81">2) Graphics
                                            &lt;personality&gt; Node Install</nameliteral></dt>
                                    <dd id="82">
                                        <p id="83">Use the console port in graphics mode to
                                            display messages. This selection works with most console
                                            displays.</p>
                                    </dd>
                                </dlentry>
                                <dlentry id="84">
                                    <dt id="85"><nameliteral id="86">3) Graphics
                                            Text &lt;personality&gt; Node Install</nameliteral></dt>
                                    <dd id="87">
                                        <p id="88">Use the console port in text mode to
                                            display messages. This is a safe option for nodes that
                                            do not support graphics mode.</p>
                                    </dd>
                                </dlentry>
                            </dl>
                            <p id="93">If you do not change the selection, the default is
                                applied automatically after a few seconds.</p>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep id="wait_for_login_prompt" id="116">
                        <cmd id="117">Wait while the node is configured and rebooted.</cmd>
                        <info id="118">
                            <p id="122">After a few minutes, the node is reported as <uicontrol id="123">Locked</uicontrol>, <uicontrol id="125">Disabled</uicontrol>, and <uicontrol id="127">Online</uicontrol> in the<uicontrol id="101">
                                    Hosts</uicontrol> list.</p>
                            <note id="note_N10263_N1025C_N10255_N10119_N1010F_N100BF_N10029_N10001" id="120" type="caution">
                                <p id="121">To ensure a successful installation, wait for
                                    the node to be reported as <uicontrol id="124">Locked</uicontrol>, <uicontrol id="126">Disabled</uicontrol>, and <uicontrol id="128">Online</uicontrol>, and ensure that the login prompt
                                    appears on the host console. If the process is interrupted
                                    prematurely, the host installation can fail.</p>
                            </note>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
                <stepresult id="node_locked_available_online" id="110">
                    <p id="97">The host is now configured with a personality.</p>
                </stepresult>
            </step>
        </steps>
        <result id="assign-result" id="102">
            <p id="103">The new host is initialized with an operating system, rebooted, and
                configured with the assigned personality.</p>
        </result>
    </rcbody>
